 <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/27/01 2:24:39 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Clerics-Peridots and You (open discussion)</span><hr size=1> This is an idea that I've thinking about for quite some time, but the only way it would work is for it to become socially acceptable.<br>
<br>
Tired of clerics wanting those gems in OS?<br>
Tired of hearing clerics complain about high Peridot costs?<br>
<br>
If you are, then I propose a solution to this age old problem.<br>
<br>
The next time you are in town, stop by the local gem merchant and purchase a stack or 2 of peridots. Then, when you are in a group and would like a symbol hand a peridot to the cleric and ask for a symbol when manna allows. This can also be used for runes.<br>
<br>
Now the gems are evenly distributed to all in the group, and noone can be mad about clerics getting the first couple.<br>
<br>
Lets take this to another zone and see what happens. Lets go to HS for instance. Hmm, no gems are dropping here. Tank_01 says,&quot;Need symbol&quot; The cleric says,&quot;Sure, give me a peridot and I'll hook you up!&quot; In a zone like this currently there is no way for a cleric to regain his costs, and usually leaves the zone down a little on pp. Add this up over a week or 2 and walla! The cleric is flat broke with a dwindling peridot supply. <br>
<br>
I guess the point I'm trying to make is that most people can join a pickup group and have fun with little or no expense, while the cleric can't say quite so much.<br>
<br>
Closing thoughts:<br>
<br>
Not every zone drops gems<br>
Not every cleric is rich<br>
If someone wants a symbol, why should the cleric pay for it?<br>
<br>
I'd like to here any views on this subject as I've thought it over and I don't see where splitting the costs hurts anyone. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/utreage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Treage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Visitor</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/27/01 2:33:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:Clerics-Peridots and You (open discussion</span><hr size=1> Can this be moved to the general discussion please?<br>
