<br>
     Regardless, if gem drops started out quite fast, I'd take about 10 decent quality gems, and the rest would get alpha randomed to the group. That way I'd cover the price of the 40 peridots I'd brought along for that hunt, the price to restock whatever I'd use on that particular hunt, and to cover any losses I'd had on a previous hunt where the drops were not so good. On average it worked very well. Almost no complaints really. <br>
But, different groups have different practices.<br>
